Enablement of Gemini Enterprise in blank GCP Project 

You enable Gemini Enterprise in a blank GCP project mainly by: -  

Turning on billing, Enabling the right Gemini/Vertex-related APIs, and Assigning the required IAM roles to users. 

Prerequisites (Org / Workspace) 

Ensure your Google Workspace or Cloud org has aтАпGemini Enterprise subscriptionтАпand licenses assigned to users who should use Gemini Enterprise. 

Make sure you can create projects and enable services (for you: roles likeтАпProject CreatorтАпandтАпService Usage AdminтАпare sufficient) 

Step 1: CREATE a blank GCP Project 

Go to the Google Cloud console project selector and clickтАпNew Project. 

Enter project name, organization, and location; clickтАпCreate. 

Wait until the project is created and then select it in the top project selector. 

Step 2: Enable billing on the Project 

In the Cloud console, go toтАпBillingтАпand either link an existing billing account or create a new one. 

Confirm that billing status for the project shows as active; Gemini Enterprise usage requires billing/quota tracking 

Step 3: Enable required APIs 

From the console: 

With the new project selected, go toтАпAPIs & Services тЖТ Library. 

Enable at minimum: 

Gemini for Google Cloud APIтАп(cloudaicompanion.googleapis.com) тАУ required for Gemini Code Assist / Gemini in Cloud Tools. 

Vertex AI APIтАптАУ if you will call Gemini models from Vertex AI endpoints.тАЛ 

Cloud Storage APIтАптАУ if you will store data, prompts, or artifacts.тАЛ 

Identity and Access Management (IAM) APIтАптАУ to manage IAM programmatically.тАЛ 

For Gemini EnterpriseтАЩs intranet/agentic features, also ensure theтАпGemini EnterpriseтАп(Discovery EngineтАУbacked) service is enabled as indicated in the Gemini Enterprise get-started guide. 

Step 4: Grant IAM roles in the project 

Assign these roles to each user (or group) who should use Gemini from this project: 

Gemini for Google Cloud User:тАпroles/cloudaicompanion.userтАптАУ lets users invoke Gemini for Google Cloud features.тАЛ 

For Vertex AI Gemini usage: 

Vertex AI User:тАпroles/aiplatform.user.тАЛ 

For admins who manage setup: 

Service Usage Admin:тАпroles/serviceusage.serviceUsageAdminтАпto enable APIs. 

OptionallyтАпOwnerтАпorтАпEditorтАпon the project for full control. 

Step 5: Turn on Gemini Enterprise experience 

In the Cloud console, search forтАпGemini EnterpriseтАпor open the Gemini Enterprise page (if available in your region/tenant). 

If you see aтАпStart trialтАпorтАпEnableтАпbutton, click it to activate Gemini Enterprise for the selected project (or the org, depending on UI). 

Follow the prompts to connect data stores (e.g., Google Drive, Calendar) or deploy a Gemini Enterprise app if youтАЩre using the full intranet/assistant experience. 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

SHAREPOINT ONLINE CONNECTOR SETUP 

Before creating the Microsoft SharePoint connector in Gemini Enterprise, register a Microsoft Entra application to enable secure access. Google recommends that you use Federated credentials authentication method that you select when you are creating the connector in Gemini Enterprise. 

Step 1: CREATE APP REGISTRATION  

Create an App registration in the Microsoft Entra admin center: https://entra.microsoft.com 

Under Supported account types, select the option Accounts in the organizational directory only 

Under Redirect URI, add a Web redirect URI pointing to the Google Cloud auth handler https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/console/oauth/sharepoint_oauth.html 

 

 

After creating the App registration, note the Client ID and Tenant ID: 

